@user1:
The leading `\n` here causes an excess newline when there are mixed HTTP/DNS challenges. It could be avoided by making it conditional on there being any `http01_achalls`.


@author:
This would only be an issue when Certbot actually would support mixed challenge types. Is that the case?

@user1:
    certbot certonly --manual -d example.com -d "*.example.com" --manual-auth-hook /bin/true --debug-challenges

is one way to produce a mixed challenge type scenario.

@author:
Ah, cool, I did not know that. I thought the challenge type function would prefer having all challenges of the same type when I looked at the code, but perhaps it gives priority to what preference the authenticator has.

Anyway, fixed the newline issue without requiring it to be conditional :slightly_smiling_face:

@user1:
I appreciate the flavor here 😆 .

It's not a big deal, but do you think the message will get across to more people if we call it the "internet"?

@author:
Not sure if people wouldn't understand "world wide web", but it's probably good to err on the side of caution, thanks :slightly_smiling_face:
